#: ../../hosting/administration/user-authentication.rst:7
msgid "User Authentication"
msgstr "Authentification utilisateur"

#: ../../hosting/administration/user-authentication.rst:9
msgid ""
"This section describes how to configure and manage user authentication in "
"Parsec."
msgstr ""
"Cette section décrit comment configurer et gérer l'authentification "
"utilisateur dans Parsec."

#: ../../hosting/administration/user-authentication.rst:11
msgid ""
"As described in the :ref:`Authentication "
"<doc_hosting_client_deploy_authentication>` section, user authentication is "
"(mostly) a client-side operation in Parsec: it determines the way the user's "
"local device file will be protected. Please refer to that section for more "
"details."
msgstr ""
"Comme décrit dans la section :ref:`Authentication "
"<doc_hosting_client_deploy_authentication>`, l'authentification utilisateur "
"dans Parsec est une opération qui a lieu (principalement) côté client : elle "
"détermine la façon dont un fichier d'appareil local sera protégé. Cette "
"section peut être consultée pour plus de détails."

#: ../../hosting/administration/user-authentication.rst:16
msgid ""
"Parsec also supports :abbr:`MFA (Multi-Factor Authentication)` via :abbr:"
"`TOTP (Time-based One-Time Password)` codes. This is in addition to the "
"primary protection (password, keyring, etc.)."
msgstr ""
"Parsec propose aussi du :abbr:`MFA (Authentification Multi Facteurs)` via "
"un :abbr:`TOTP (mot de passe à usage unique basé sur le temps)`, en plus "
"d'une protection primaire (mot de passe, keyring, etc.)."

#: ../../hosting/administration/user-authentication.rst:23
msgid "Authentication advisories"
msgstr "Authentification recommandée"

#: ../../hosting/administration/user-authentication.rst:27
msgid ""
"When starting the server, the recommended authentication methods can be "
"specified as shown in the example below."
msgstr ""
"Lorsqu'un serveur est démarré, des méthodes d'authentification peuvent être "
"configurées, comme dans l'exemple ci dessous."

#: ../../hosting/administration/user-authentication.rst:36
msgid "Possible values are :"
msgstr "Les valeurs possibles sont :"

#: ../../hosting/administration/user-authentication.rst:38
msgid "`PASSWORD`"
msgstr "`PASSWORD`"

#: ../../hosting/administration/user-authentication.rst:39
msgid "`PASSWORD+TOTP`"
msgstr "`PASSWORD+TOTP`"

#: ../../hosting/administration/user-authentication.rst:40
msgid "`KEYRING`"
msgstr "`KEYRING`"

#: ../../hosting/administration/user-authentication.rst:41
msgid "`KEYRING+TOTP`"
msgstr "`KEYRING+TOTP`"

#: ../../hosting/administration/user-authentication.rst:42
msgid "`PKI`"
msgstr "`PKI`"

#: ../../hosting/administration/user-authentication.rst:43
msgid "`PKI+TOTP`"
msgstr "`PKI+TOTP`"

#: ../../hosting/administration/user-authentication.rst:44
msgid "`OPENBAO`"
msgstr "`OPENBAO`"

#: ../../hosting/administration/user-authentication.rst:45
msgid "`OPENBAO+TOTP`"
msgstr "`OPENBAO+TOTP`"

#: ../../hosting/administration/user-authentication.rst:49
msgid ""
"Only the specified methods will be available for users in Parsec client "
"application."
msgstr ""
"Seules les méthodes spécifiées vont être disponibles pour les utilisateurs "
"de l'application client Parsec"

#: ../../hosting/administration/user-authentication.rst:51
msgid ""
"However, since the encrypted device file is only available locally, the "
"Parsec Server cannot *enforce* the specified methods (hence the *advisory* "
"name)."
msgstr ""
" Cependant, comme le fichier d'appareil chiffré est uniquement local, le "
"serveurParsec ne peut pas *imposer* les méthodes spécifiées (d'où le nom de "
"méthodes *recommandées*)."

#: ../../hosting/administration/user-authentication.rst:54
msgid ""
"MFA is a special case because it involves communication with the Parsec "
"Server. If you want to force users to enable MFA use *only* the variant "
"including ``+TOTP`` (e.g. ``PASSWORD+TOTP``, but not ``PASSWORD``)"
msgstr ""
"Le MFA est est un cas particulier parce qu'il implique une communication "
"avec le serveur Parsec. Si vous souhaitez forcer les utilisateurs à activer "
"le MFA, vous devez utiliser *uniquement* les variants qui contiennent "
"``+TOTP`` (par exemple : ``PASSWORD+TOTP``, mais pas ``PASSWORD``)"

#: ../../hosting/administration/user-authentication.rst:61
msgid "MFA setup reset"
msgstr "Réinitialisation de la configuration MFA"

#: ../../hosting/administration/user-authentication.rst:63
msgid ""
"When a user loses access to their authenticator app (e.g. lost or replaced "
"phone), their MFA setup must be reset by a **server administrator** before "
"the user can reconfigure it (see :ref:`doc_userguide_mfa`)."
msgstr ""
"Lorsqu'un utilisateur perd l'accès à son application d'authentification (par "
"exemple, en cas de perte ou de remplacement de son téléphone), sa "
"configuration MFA doit être réinitialisée par un **administrateur de "
"serveur** avant que l'utilisateur puisse la reconfigurer (voir :ref:"
"`doc_userguide_mfa`)."

#: ../../hosting/administration/user-authentication.rst:67
msgid "To reset a user's MFA setup, the server administrator needs to provide:"
msgstr ""
"Pour réinitialiser la configuration MFA d'un utilisateur, l'administrateur "
"du serveur doit fournir :"

#: ../../hosting/administration/user-authentication.rst:69
msgid "The Parsec server address, as a Parsec URL ``parsec3://hostname:port``"
msgstr ""
"L'adresse du serveur Parsec, en tant qu'URL Parsec ``parsec3://hostname:"
"port``"

#: ../../hosting/administration/user-authentication.rst:70
msgid "The ``administration_token`` configured on the Parsec server"
msgstr "Le ``administration_token`` configuré sur le serveur Parsec"

#: ../../hosting/administration/user-authentication.rst:71
msgid "The organization ID"
msgstr "L'ID de l'organisation"

#: ../../hosting/administration/user-authentication.rst:72
msgid ""
"The user to reset, identified by their email address or their Parsec user ID"
msgstr ""
"L'utilisateur à réinitialiser, identifié par son adresse e-mail ou son ID "
"d'utilisateur Parsec"

#: ../../hosting/administration/user-authentication.rst:74
msgid "Typically to reset by email address:"
msgstr "Typiquement, pour réinitialiser par adresse e-mail :"

